Package com.davidbracewell.parsing.handlers

Commonly used expression handlers used for parsing

See: Description

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AssignmentHandler
    Creates AssignmentExpressions where the object in the left expressions is being assigned the value of the right expression using the given assignment operator.
    BinaryOperatorHandler
    Creates BinaryOperatorExpressions where the left and right expressions are being operated on by the operator represented by the current token.
    CommentHandler
    Creates a comment expression where the everything from the comment token to the end of line (specified via the endOfLine token type) is found.
    GroupHandler
    Treats everything between the open group type and closed group type as a single group which should result in a single expression.
    InfixHandler
    Abstract based handler for infix operations.
    MethodCallHandler
    Creates MethodCallExpressions where the current token denotes the token type the signifies a method call and the left token is the method name.
    ParserHandler
    Abstract base class for all parser handlers.
    PostfixOperatorHandler
    Captures PostfixOperatorExpressions where the current token is the operator and the previous expression is what is being operated on.
    PrefixHandler
    Abstract base class for prefix handlers.
    PrefixOperatorHandler
    Creates PrefixOperatorExpressions where the current token is the operator and the next expression is what the operator is operating on.
    PrefixSkipHandler
    A handler that defines the token type should be ignored.
    ValueHandler
    Creates ValueExpressions which simply wrap the type and text of the current token.
